From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ws63-rs <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 7 Jun 2026 16:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] hw/riscv: register the HiSilicon BS21 machine

Build-system integration for hw/riscv/bs21.c (the BS21 / BS2X machine, copied
into the tree alongside this series). bs21.c reuses the shared HiSilicon riscv31
device models from ws63.c via hisi_riscv31.h, so CONFIG_BS21 selects CONFIG_WS63
(which compiles ws63.c and the shared models). The full split into a dedicated
CONFIG_HISI_RISCV31 source set + the `hisi-riscv31` CPU rename is deferred to the
connectivity-generalization pass.

Adds the CONFIG_BS21 meson source entry and the Kconfig symbol (default y on
RISCV32, selects UNIMP + WS63). Registers `-M bs21`.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 hw/riscv/Kconfig     | 7 +++++++
 hw/riscv/meson.build | 1 +
 2 files changed, 8 insertions(+)
diff --git a/hw/riscv/Kconfig b/hw/riscv/Kconfig
--- a/hw/riscv/Kconfig
+++ b/hw/riscv/Kconfig
@@ -126,6 +126,13 @@ config WS63
     depends on RISCV32
     select UNIMP
 
+config BS21
+    bool
+    default y
+    depends on RISCV32
+    select UNIMP
+    select WS63
+
 config XIANGSHAN_KUNMINGHU
     bool
     default y
diff --git a/hw/riscv/meson.build b/hw/riscv/meson.build
--- a/hw/riscv/meson.build
+++ b/hw/riscv/meson.build
@@ -19,4 +19,5 @@ riscv_ss.add(when: 'CONFIG_RISCV_MIPS_CPS', if_true: files('cps.c'))
 riscv_ss.add(when: 'CONFIG_MIPS_BOSTON_AIA', if_true: files('boston-aia.c'))
 
 riscv_ss.add(when: 'CONFIG_WS63', if_true: files('ws63.c'))
+riscv_ss.add(when: 'CONFIG_BS21', if_true: files('bs21.c'))
 hw_arch += {'riscv': riscv_ss}

